{
  "_comment": "The app's frontend uses modern ES2020+ (const, arrow functions, async/await, template literals). JSHint defaults to ES5 and flags every const/let as a syntax error. Vendor files under static/vendor/ are third-party bundles we do not lint.",
  "_comment_globals": "Browser globals Codacy's older JSHint dictionary omits even with browser:true: URLSearchParams, EventSource, AbortController, DOMException, TextDecoderStream. Declare explicitly.",
  "_comment_expr": "expr (W030) fires on optional-chaining expression heads like `err?.status` — Codacy's JSHint doesn't fully model ES2020 optional chaining even with esversion:11; the pattern itself is valid.",
  "esversion": 11,
  "browser": true,
  "devel": true,
  "module": true,
  "asi": true,
  "expr": true,
  "globals": {
    "URLSearchParams": false,
    "EventSource": false,
    "AbortController": false,
    "DOMException": false,
    "TextDecoderStream": false
  }
}
